  "content": {
    "problemStatement": "You\u2019re given an array AAA of size NNN.\n\nCount the number of quadruples (L1,R1,L2,R2)(L_1,R_1,L_2,R_2)(L1\u200b,R1\u200b,L2\u200b,R2\u200b) satisfying:\n\n\n1\u2264L1\u2264R1&lt;L2\u2264R2\u2264N1 \\le L_1 \\le R_1 \\lt L_2 \\le R_2 \\le N1\u2264L1\u200b\u2264R1\u200b&lt;L2\u200b\u2264R2\u200b\u2264N;\ngcd\u2061(AL1,\u2026,AR1)\u00d7gcd\u2061(AL2,\u2026,AR2)\\gcd(A_{L_1},\\ldots ,A_{R_1}) \\times \\gcd(A_{L_2},\\ldots,A_{R_2})gcd(AL1\u200b\u200b,\u2026,AR1\u200b\u200b)\u00d7gcd(AL2\u200b\u200b,\u2026,AR2\u200b\u200b) is a perfect square. Note that gcd\u2061\\gcdgcd denoted the greatest common divisor.\nSince the answer may be huge, output the answer modulo 998244353998244353998244353.\n\n\nInput Format\n\nThe first line of input will contain a single integer TTT, denoting the number of test cases.\nEach test case consists of two lines of input.\n\nThe first line of each test case contains an integer NNN.\nThe second lines contains NNN integers A1,A2,\u2026,ANA_1,A_2,\\ldots,A_NA1\u200b,A2\u200b,\u2026,AN\u200b.\n\n\n\n\nOutput Format\nFor each test case, output in a new line, the number of quadruples, modulo 998244353998244353998244353.",
    "constraints": [
      "1\u2264T\u22641051 \\leq T \\leq 10^51\u2264T\u2264105",
      "2\u2264N\u22644\u22c51052 \\leq N \\leq 4 \\cdot 10^52\u2264N\u22644\u22c5105",
      "1\u2264Ai\u22641071 \\leq A_i \\leq 10^71\u2264Ai\u200b\u2264107",
      "The sum of NNN over all test cases won't exceed 4\u22c51054 \\cdot 10^54\u22c5105."
    ],
    "inputFormat": "",
    "outputFormat": "",
    "sampleTestCases": [
      {
        "id": "sample_1",
        "input": "3\n3\n2 6 8\n4\n1 1 1 1\n5\n24 18 54 12 36",
        "output": "3\n15\n8",
        "explanation": "Explanation:\nTest Case 111: There are 333 valid quadruples (L1,R1,L2,R2)(L_1,R_1,L_2,R_2)(L1\u200b,R1\u200b,L2\u200b,R2\u200b):\n\n(1,1,3,3)(1,1,3,3)(1,1,3,3): gcd\u2061(A1,A1)\u00d7gcd\u2061(A3,A3)=2\u00d78=16=42\\gcd(A_1,A_1) \\times \\gcd(A_3,A_3)=2 \\times 8=16=4^2gcd(A1\u200b,A1\u200b)\u00d7gcd(A3\u200b,A3\u200b)=2\u00d78=16=42.\n(1,1,2,3)(1,1,2,3)(1,1,2,3): gcd\u2061(A1,A1)\u00d7gcd\u2061(A2,A3)=2\u00d72=4=22\\gcd(A_1,A_1) \\times \\gcd(A_2,A_3)=2 \\times 2=4=2^2gcd(A1\u200b,A1\u200b)\u00d7gcd(A2\u200b,A3\u200b)=2\u00d72=4=22.\n(1,2,3,3)(1,2,3,3)(1,2,3,3): gcd\u2061(A1,A2)\u00d7gcd\u2061(A3,A3)=2\u00d78=16=42\\gcd(A_1,A_2) \\times \\gcd(A_3,A_3)=2 \\times 8=16=4^2gcd(A1\u200b,A2\u200b)\u00d7gcd(A3\u200b,A3\u200b)=2\u00d78=16=42."
      }
    ]
